Overall, we all liked this recipe, which is saying quite a bit, since "all" includes 2 40-something New Yorkers and a two year old. Two thoughts for everyone. First, we halved the recipe, which worked pretty well except that it needed a bit more liquid. Next time, I'd probably go with 1 1/8th cups milk, which is 50% plus 1/4 cup. Second, it largely but not entirely passes the "great leftover recipe!" test. It transforms the leftover you're bored with into something pretty yummy, which is very good. But it requires a lot of new ingredients, thus creating more leftovers than it uses, and it's got more steps and pans to it than it should, three pans and one bowl. So, go for it... but don't expect it to be superquick or supereasy.

