Rating: 1
One of the best cooking compliments I have ever had was about my turkey tetrazzini (the second was my pecan pie after people had visited New Orleans!). I have loved this dish ever since my mother "cheated" and bought a Stouffers! However, this recipe omits the MAIN ingredient : celery. Sauté the mushrooms and celery (tons of both - and I mean tons!) in butter and then add the white wine. Simmer until very soft, then add your broth/white sauce mixture, with the turkey (shredded by hand). (My secret for the buttered crumb topping : freeze french bread loafs, then put in the food processor (frozen!) for perfect fresh bread crumbs - sauté in salted butter. The "Joy of Cooking" has a very good basic recipe. I have spent years improving it. I am serving it to 10 French people Saturday night!

